FSA Abandons Proposed Tougher Rule for Mortgages, Times Reports

-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n
-- 
2011-03-23T00:15:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/fsa-abandons-proposed-tougher-rule-for-mortgages-times-reports.html
The Financial Services Authority is
dropping a proposed rule that would have required lenders to
reject mortgage applicants unable to demonstrate the ability to
repay the loan within 25 years, the London-based Times reported,
citing FSA Chief Executive Officer  Hector Sants . The rule was to
have applied even if the loan were for 30 years, the newspaper
said.    Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
